Subject: [PATCH] libarchive: remove unused zstd.h include from
 archive_read_support_filter.c

The zstd.h header is not required by archive_read_support_filter.c.
Removing it avoids build issues on systems where the zstd development
headers are unavailable or incompatible.

---
 subprojects/libarchive-3.7.2/libarchive/archive_read_support_filter.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/subprojects/libarchive-3.7.2/libarchive/archive_read_support_filter.c b/subprojects/libarchive-3.7.2/libarchive/archive_read_support_filter.c
index XXXXXXX..YYYYYYY 100644
--- a/subprojects/libarchive-3.7.2/libarchive/archive_read_support_filter.c
+++ b/subprojects/libarchive-3.7.2/libarchive/archive_read_support_filter.c
@@
-#include <zstd.h>

